rged from Al Capone's criminal confederation. Focusing on the murder of Zuckerman by Patrick, Kraus introduces us to the different models of organized crime they represented, a raft of largely forgotten Jewish gangsters, and the changing nature of Chicago's political corruption. Hard-to-believe anecdotes of corrupt politicians, seasoned killers, and in-over-their-heads criminal operators spotlight the magnitude and importance of Jewish gangsters to the story of Windy City mob rule.With an eye for the dramatic, The Kosher Capones takes us deep inside a hidden society and offers glimpses of the men who ran the Jewish criminal community in Chicago for more than sixty years.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aGangsterszIllinoiszChicagoxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewish criminalszIllinoiszChicagovBiography. 0aJewish criminalszIllinoiszChicagoxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewszIllinoiszChicagoxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewszIllinoiszChicagoxSocial conditionsy20th century. 0aOrganized crimezIllinoiszChicagoxHistoryy20th century. 4aCriminology. 4aJewish Studies. 4aU.S. History. 7aHISTORY / United States / 20th Century.2bisacsh  aorganized crime, American Jewish history, Jewish studies, Chicago history, criminal justice.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065198008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019 Englishz978311061017808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019z9783110606195oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501747335zCo-access DOI >> click